results.name: Let z = A084937: a(n) = number of odd numbers <= z(n) that are != z(k) for k=1..n-1 and not coprime to z(n-1) and z(n-2).
program: f x y zs = g zs [] where
g (v:vs) ws | gcd v y > 1 || gcd v x > 1 = g vs (v : ws)
| otherwise = ws : f v x (delete v zs)
xref: For a different way to look at the missing numbers in A084937, see A249686, A250099, A250100.
